body:
I'd like to point out that the new `git://` tests are not actually running. That's because they require `git-daemon` which is not installed by default.

@cevich I know you've been busy building new CI VMs, and I'm sorry to catch this so late, but when you next build VMs could you please make sure they rpm- and apt-install `git-daemon`?

@jnovy same thing needs to happen with buildah and podman specfiles, in the `-tests` subpackage.
